text:
The intent of a significant portion of the bad actors on Twitter and social media is simply put, to divide America and create discord. In short, to make discourse and therefore governing impossible, and to make you distrust your neighbor.

My fear is not that bigots are taking over (they are, that's not in dispute), it's that when I see a truck rolling down the street with an American flag flying from the back of it, I'm starting to assume the driver is a bigot. Which is exactly the kind of assumption and hate our adversaries are trying to create.

My overall message, which I was honestly shocked to find controversial, was simply that the statement "half of all Americans are evil" isn't just inaccurate,  it's dangerous. Making people's lives on social media a living nightmare just because their politics are different than yours isn't doing anything productive, it's very much the opposite. Dismissing anyone you disagree with as a bigot is an easy trap, especially when you follow that up by believing it and therefore ignoring any statement they would make as poison.
I’d you think anyone is blankly assuming a flag in your truck makes you a bigot then maybe you’re the one falling for the right’s propaganda about the left.
I'm not the flag truck here, dana.
And I don’t call anyone I disagree with a a bigot nor does anyone I know. We just call bigots bigots, and half the voters voted for one.
And you assuming I am because I'd vote for Biden over Bernie is really kind of scary.
I didn’t say you were but you seem concerned people are doing things they aren’t.
How did I assume you’d vote any direction in any words I wrote?
>A flag in your truck makes you a bigot
Once again for a guy concerned about people falling for propaganda you seem really into asserting people are doing things they aren’t doing
You wrote that!
And you added "you" and "your" to it.
Glad we quarantined this!
The only thing i ask is yall walk away from the channel fine with each other. If i (or anyone) spoke as freely as this for long enough i bet i could get you to hate me too.
